Parliament, Tuesday, 17 September 2019 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations (SCOA) will tomorrow have deliberations on Special Appropriation Bill [B10-2019], including submissions and proposed amendments received.
	
	The Bill provides for the appropriation of an additional amount of money for the requirements of the Department of Public Enterprises to assist Eskom Holdings SOC Limited with its financial obligations and to provide for matters connected therewith.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Wednesday, 17 September 2019
	Time: 10 am 
	Venue: Committee Room V119, First Floor, Old Assembly Building
	
	Meanwhile, the Portfolio Committee on Defence and Military Veterans is scheduled to receive a briefing from the Department of Defence (DOD) and the Department of Military Veterans (DMV) on its 2019 first quarterly reports. Furthermore, the DOD and the DMV will provide feedback on the recommendations made by the committee in its 2019 budget report.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Wednesday, 17 September 2019
	Time: 10 am 
	Venue: Committee Room M514, Fifth Floor, Marks Building
	
